-- Red Sox Beat Rays 12-2 After Pirates Even MLB Series With Cards
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2013-10-04T22:45:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-04/red-sox-beat-rays-12-2-after-pirates-even-mlb-series-with-cards.html
Jonny Gomes and Jarrod Saltalamacchia
had two-run doubles as the Boston Red Sox defeated the Tampa Bay
Rays 12-2 in the opener of their best-of-five American League
division series.  Jon Lester  allowed two runs on three hits in 7 2/3 innings
for the host Red Sox at Fenway Park. Game 2 in the series is set
for tomorrow, also in Boston.  In the National League, rookie Gerrit Cole allowed two hits
in six innings while Pedro Alvarez and Starling Marte hit home
runs for Pittsburgh as the Pirates beat the St. Louis Cardinals
7-1 to even their playoff series at one game apiece.  Game 3 in the Pirates-Cardinals series is set for Oct. 6 in
Pittsburgh.  The other two Major League Baseball division series have
games tonight. The Los Angeles Dodgers are at Atlanta, trying to
take a 2-0 lead against the Braves in their NL series. In the
AL, the  Detroit Tigers  visit the  Oakland Athletics  for their
series opener.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  